news.title: Waterfield Advisors leases office space at Avighna House in Mumbai at record rentals
news.para: The firm has leased over 6,150 sq ft usable office space in the tower for a total term of five years. The deal assumes significance in the backdrop of the record per sq ft rentals attracted by any office property in the country’s most expensive market of Mumbai after a long gap.

news.title: Madhya Pradesh HC seeks norms for buildings along Narmada
news.para: Hearing a petition filed by Dayoday Seva Kendra alleging violation of no-construction norm within 300 metres on the banks of river Narmada, the division bench of Chief Justice R V Malimath and Justice Vishal Mishra issued the directives.

news.title: Buyers to pay 18% GST on plots bought from AUDA & Ahmedabad civic body
news.para: ​For almost a year now state GST officials have been issuing notices to the Ahmedabad Urban Development Authority and the Ahmedabad Municipal Corporation, asking them to recover 18% GST from the buyer who bought a plot from these civic bodies last year.

news.title: Maharashtra government set to increase bid for Air India building to Rs 1,600 crore
news.para: The state plans to expand Mantralaya into the Air India building. Last month, deputy chief minister Fadnavis said that the state government was facing a space crunch to house government offices in Mantralaya and the annexe building.

news.title: MHADA may hike earnest deposits for MIG, HIG flats
news.para: The proposal, which will be soon placed before the housing authority, aims to charge 10% of the total cost of flat under the MHADA scheme so as to ensure applications from only genuine buyers.

news.title: MREAT orders Indiabulls' subsidiary & Lucina Land Development to refund buyer's money
news.para: The complainant, Sushila Gautam, had booked a flat in Indiabulls Green in 2013 and the promoter had agreed to execute an agreement for sale within 24 months of signing the booking form.

news.title: Six years on, MahaRERA yet to clear over 6,000 complaints
news.para: Though MahaRERA has been working on identifying the “lapsed” projects, consumers feel the complaints need to be addressed at the earliest by setting up more benches across the state and ensuring more hearings.

news.title: Kalyan: Five held in RERA scam remanded in two-day police custody
news.para: The accused even through forged prepared building permission documents had managed to get RERA certificates on behalf of developers and using the same builder managed to sell their illegal flats in buildings.

news.title: Tamil Nadu government notifies rules to deal with illegal constructions
news.para: The rules state that if the authority comes to know about an unauthorised construction, a notice should be issued seeking documents related to the property.

news.title: Gurugram: Two towers illegal, Pyramid Infrastructure to pay Rs 50,000 to each buyer
news.para: Terming the two towers illegal, the Haryana Real Estate Regulatory Authority (H-Rera) has directed the developer to refund interest-free security, labour cess and other charges collected from buyers.

news.title: Mahindra Lifespace sale bookings grow 32% to Rs 399 crore in Q2 FY23
news.para: Mahindra Lifespace, a part of business conglomerate Mahindra Group, reported an over two-fold jump in sale bookings at Rs 1,001 crore for April-September 2022-23 from Rs 449 crore in the year-ago period.

news.title: Gurugram administration to demolish Chintels Paradiso's Tower-D
news.para: Gurugram Deputy Commissioner Nishant Kumar Yadav, while sharing the report of the IIT team on Saturday, said the team has found structural deficiencies in the construction of the tower, whose repair is not possible on technical and economic grounds.

news.title: Vaishnavi Group to redevelop Bengaluru's Chalukya Hotel into grade-A office
news.para: Redevelopment of the property, which is owned by Mohammed Iqbal, is expected to take two years from the time the requisite approvals are in. It will offer 150,000 sq. ft. of office space, the people cited earlier said.

news.title: Ozone Group to restructure loan by selling commercial, residential assets
news.para: The Bengaluru-headquartered firm, which has over Rs 4,000 crore debt on its books, is in talks with developers and investors to sell its assets and pare its debt.

news.title: Over 200 buildings in Uttar Pradesh are without fire NOC, suggests data
news.para: The data suggests that these buildings do not have the mandatory no objection certificate (NOC) from the fire safety department.
